<item>
            <title>[SOLR-10692] Split Streaming Expressions docs into more manageable parts</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-10692</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Streaming Expressions page is too big and a mix of How To and Reference materials. It should be split up a bit to make it easier to use.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;First pass at this will split all the expression types into new pages according to the type, so there will be 3 new sub-pages:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Stream Sources&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Stream Decorators&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Stream Evaluators&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Once that&apos;s done, we&apos;ll see if there&apos;s more we can do with this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attn &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=joel.bernstein&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;joel.bernstein&quot;&gt;joel.bernstein&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
